Totteham manager Mauricio Pochettino has urged supporters to stop booing Emmanuel Adebayor ahead of Saturday’s clash against Arsenal.

The Togolese striker came close to leaving White Hart Lane on transfer deadline day but saw a loan move to West Ham thwarted by chairman Daniel Levy, while the forward rejected moves to Queens Park Rangers and Crystal Palace.

Adebayor has been targeted by supporters in recent weeks following comments made by the former Arsenal striker criticising Spurs fans. 

