Meanwhile, Southampton boss Ronald Koeman has responded light-heartedly to claims from former Saints manager Pochettino that he inherited a ‘winning team’ when he took over at St Mary’s in the summer.

Speaking to Catalan radio, Pochettino said: ‘You have to say that they invested close to 80million euros (£59.8million) in the summer and it was already a winning team on the up.

‘When we arrived at Southampton in January of 2013 they had the team that had conceded the most goals in the league. It was a team with a lot of problems, with players like Adam Lallana who wasn’t playing and Luke Shaw who wasn’t playing but in one and a half years we turned it round.’

But Koemansaid: ‘He is free to give his opinions, I’m happy in Southampton and thank you Mauricio; I have an easy job!’

